  "response": "In 2016, some of the best smaller Android smartphones around 4.5-4.7 inches included:\n\n1. Sony Xperia Z5 Compact\n- 4.6-inch display\n- High-end performance\n- Waterproof design\n- Good camera\n\n2. Samsung Galaxy S7\n- 5.1-inch display (slightly larger but compact)\n- Excellent camera\n- Water-resistant\n- High-end specs\n\n3. Google Nexus 5X\n- 5.2-inch display\n- Pure Android experience\n- Good performance\n- Reasonable price\n\n4. iPhone SE\n- 4-inch display\n- While technically an iPhone, it ran iOS\n- Compact and powerful\n\n5. Samsung Galaxy A3 (2016)\n- 4.7-inch display\n- Mid-range smartphone\n- Good build quality\n- Affordable\n\nThese phones offered good performance, cameras, and somewhat compact sizes during 2016. The market was transitioning to larger displays, so truly small high-end smartphones were becoming less common.\n\nNote that \"best\" can depend on individual preferences like budget, camera quality, performance, and specific features.",
